Use the standard library
This is how to filter_by_prefix of strings and prefix:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that i is 0

   Do this strings' length times:
      Remember that s is item i in strings
      Remember that matches is yes

      When s's length is less than prefix's length, then:
         Remember that matches is no
      But, if not:
         Remember that j is 0
         Do this prefix's length times:
            When item j in s is not item j in prefix, then:
               Remember that matches is no
               Leave the loop
            End when
            Increase j
         End do
      End when

      When matches is yes, then:
         Add result to s
      End when

      Increase i
   End do

   The answer is result
Now you know